div.head:
290. Memorandum of Conversation for the RecordSource: Reagan Library, Linhard Files, JCS Breakfast, April 15, 1988. Secret;
                                Sensitive. The memorandum, which is stamped “Draft,” was drafted on
                                April 12. The meeting took place in Shultz’s office.

div.p:
Crowe: Inspection protocol;
                            no department agrees with what was tabled. Tagging is wrong. If not May
                            29, it won’t be the end of the world.
